chunks.html_content:
Find out when your tax credits payment is and how much you’ll get paid.

Tax credit payments are made every week or every 4 weeks.

You choose if you want to get paid weekly or every 4 weeks on your claim form. If you do not have a claim form, contact HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC).

If it’s a bank holiday anywhere in the UK your payment may be early.

chunks.html_content: If your payment is late, check the payment date on your award notice and contact your bank before calling HMRC.
chunks.plain_content:
Tax credits: your payment dates
Bank holiday payment dates
If your payment is late, check the payment date on your award notice and contact your bank before calling HMRC.

chunks.html_content:
Your payment might be delayed because of local holidays if you live in the following places:

  • Glasgow and Aberdeen - local holiday on 25 September
  • Edinburgh - local holiday on 18 September
  • Dundee - local holiday on 2 October

Contact your bank for more information.
